						<summary>

						<p>Door-post of the eastern entrance into the same temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Tribhº Vikrama-chōḷadēva: Year 20 = 1292-93 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription records the gift of two door-posts and a couple of steps to the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> (of the temple) by a certain woman (Veḷḷāṭṭi) named Adiyaśōḻan Araiśan <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Maṇikaiyarāyan, a <hi rend="italic">Tuḻāiyar,</hi> of Śōḻamādēvinallūr, for her own merit.</p>						

						</summary>
